How to increase productivity and performance of the application/ project you are currently a member of in your organization/ department using "Cloud Computing".

Define cloud computing and explain its evolution from traditional IT infrastructure.

Describe the key components of cloud computing, including infrastructure as a service (IaaS), platform as a service (PaaS), and software as a service (SaaS).

Explain the benefits of cloud computing, such as cost savings, scalability, flexibility, and accessibility.

Discuss the challenges associated with cloud computing, including security, privacy, data governance, and vendor lock-in.

Analyze real-world examples of cloud computing adoption in various industries, such as healthcare, finance, and education.

Compare and contrast different cloud service providers, such as Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft Azure, and Google Cloud Platform (GCP).

Discuss emerging trends in cloud computing, such as hybrid cloud, edge computing, and serverless computing.
